com.hazelcast.instance

Class GroupProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.instance.HazelcastProperties
      • com.hazelcast.instance.GroupProperties

  • public class GroupProperties
extends HazelcastProperties
    Container for configured Hazelcast properties (GroupProperty).

    A GroupProperty can be set as:

    • an environmental variable using System.setProperty(String, String)
    • the programmatic configuration using Config.setProperty(String, String)
    • the XML configuration http://docs.hazelcast.org/docs/latest-dev/manual/html-single/hazelcast-documentation.html#system-properties

    The old property definitions are deprecated since Hazelcast 3.6. Please use the new GroupProperty definitions instead.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GroupProperties

        public GroupProperties(Config config)
        Creates a container with configured Hazelcast properties.

        Uses the environmental value if no value is defined in the configuration. Uses the default value if no environmental value is defined.

        Parameters:
        config - Config used to configure the GroupProperty values.
